<p>Create the <code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">variations.py</code> Script, Make It Executable with python3.7, and Accept User Input</p>

<p>For <code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">variations.py</code>, weâ€™re going to place it in our home directory <code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">(~)</code> and we want to make sure that we can run it directly. To keep from being completely tied to the path of our python3.7 binary, we want to set up our shebang properly.</p>

<p>Letâ€™s create the file and set the shebang:</p>

