Print the Alphabetic First and Last Words from the Userâ€™s Input
Weâ€™re going to sort the words in the words list alphabetically and save the new list to sorted_words by using the sorted built-in function. Lastly, weâ€™ll print the alphabetic first and last words. Letâ€™s do this by indexing to 0 and -1.</p>

<p>~/variations.py</p>

<p>#!/usr/bin/env python3.7</p>

<p>message = input(â€œEnter a message: â€œ)</p>

<p>print(â€œLowercase:â€, message.lower())
